7 An Act relating to medical marijuana; requiring the
display of certain signage in dispensaries and
8 businesses; providing contents and requirements of
sign; requiring owners pay cost of signs; providing
9 for codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 427.30 of Title 63, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Every medical marijuana dispensary or any place medical
18 marijuana or tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) products are sold shall post
19 and display at all times a printed sign, with a minimum height of
20 eight and one-half (8 1/2) inches and a minimum width of eleven (11)
21 inches with a font size of no less than 72 points for the text, near
22 the cash register or place of checkout and at least two other highly
23 visible places in the store, which shall read as follows:
24
